criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Age is greater than 18 years old, gender is not limited

          2. Comply with ICD-10 diagnostic criteria, diagnosed with dementia, including Alzheimer's
             disease, vascular dementia, frontotemporal dementia, dementia with Lewy body, dementia
             caused by Parkinson's disease

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. senile schizophrenia;

          2. senile depression;

          3. cognitive impairment caused by endocrine system diseases (such as decreased thyroid
             and adrenal function);

          4. Cognitive impairment or dementia caused by serious diseases such as cardiovascular,
             lung, liver, kidney, and hematopoietic system;

          5. Cognitive impairment or dementia caused by alcohol, drug use, psychotropic drugs;
             6）Other physical or chemical factors that cause cognitive impairment or dementia-
